com.b2international.snowowl.snomed

Interface Component

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.cdo.CDOObject, org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.id.CDOWithID, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Concept, Description, Relationship
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ComponentImpl, ConceptImpl, DescriptionImpl, RelationshipImpl

    public interface Component
extends org.eclipse.emf.cdo.CDOObject
    Abstract representation of all SNOMED CT core components.

    The following features are supported:

    • Id
    • Active
    • Effective Time
    • Module
    • Released

    See Also:
    SnomedPackage.getComponent()

      • isActive

        boolean isActive()
        Returns wit the status of the SNOMED CT component.
        If the component is active this will return with true, if the component is retired this method will return with false.
        Returns:
        true if the component is active, otherwise it returns with false.
        See Also:
        setActive(boolean), SnomedPackage.getComponent_Active()

      • getEffectiveTime

        java.util.Date getEffectiveTime()
        Effective time is the point in time when the current SNOMED CT component has been modified.
        Can be null. If null, it means that the component has been modified but not published yet.
        For more details, please see released.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Effective Time' attribute.
        See Also:
        isSetEffectiveTime(), unsetEffectiveTime(), setEffectiveTime(Date), SnomedPackage.getComponent_EffectiveTime()

      • setEffectiveTime

        void setEffectiveTime(java.util.Date value)
        Counterpart of getEffectiveTime().
        Invoking this method with null value is identical with calling unsetEffectiveTime().
        Parameters:
        value - the new effective time for the current component. Can be null.
        See Also:
        isSetEffectiveTime(), unsetEffectiveTime(), getEffectiveTime()

      • unsetEffectiveTime

        void unsetEffectiveTime()
        Unsets the effective time of the current component.
        Identical with #setEffectiveTime(null).
        See Also:
        isSetEffectiveTime(), getEffectiveTime(), setEffectiveTime(Date)

      • isSetEffectiveTime

        boolean isSetEffectiveTime()
        Returns true if the effective time is specified on the component. Otherwise returns with false.
        Returns:
        true if the effective time is set on the component, more formally if null != getEffectiveTime(). Otherwise false.
        See Also:
        unsetEffectiveTime(), getEffectiveTime(), setEffectiveTime(Date)
